England! Because I'm a total anglophile.

So, my new geeky obsession is Being Human. It's a British show about a vampire, a werewolf, and a ghost who share a flat in Bristol. I know it kind of sounds like the setup to a bad joke, but it's actually really good. Nice mix of humor and drama. Syfy also recently started an American spinoff. For me, the best part of the show is the vampire Mitchell, played by Aiden Turner. He's so dreamy. And I love his Irish accent. *swoon* Oh my god, he's so adorable.

Sigh.

I gave in and "upgraded" my account from basic to plus because I figured they were already making me see ads, so I might as well get a few extra features. But I'm already regretting it. These ads are really distracting and intrusive. Ugh.
Wow, LJ. Pop-up ads. With video. And audio. That's not annoying and intrusive at all! Banner ads are one thing, but this shit is ridiculous.
